The Broker Digital Experience Site contains components to provide brokers with functionality for creating quotes, issuing policies, and managing policies. These components fall into three categories: FlexCard Based Components, LWCs (Lightning Web Components), and Classic Card Based Components.

Some of these components call data sources, including Omnistudio Data Mappers and Integration Procedures from the Insurance Services Catalog. The data sources come out-of-the-box with Vlocity Insurance.

The following components are available:

* FlexCard Based Components:
	+ Insurance Account Record Header Component
	+ Insurance Account Quote List Component
	+ Insurance Account Insurance Policy List Component
	+ Insurance Account (Asset) Policy List Component
	+ Insurance Quote List Component for the Homepage
	+ Insurance Insurance Policy Record Header Component
	+ Insurance Account Asset Record Header Component
	+ Insurance Quote Record Header
* LWCs:
	+ insRecordListTable
	+ insRecordHeader
	+ cfInsQuoteActions
	+ cfInsInsurancePolicyActions
	+ insTrailingDocuments
* Classic Card Based Components:
	+ Vlocity State Transition
	+ Vlocity Rules Log
	+ Vlocity Insurance Policy
	+ Vlocity Insurance Policy Insured Items
	+ Vlocity Insurance Quote
	+ Vlocity Insurance Quote Insured Items

These components use data sources such as:

* InsGetQuoteByProducer (used by Quote List on the Homepage)
* InsGetAccountInsurancePolicyList (used by Account Insurance Policy List)
* InsGetAccountPolicyList (used by Account Policy List, Asset)
* InsGetAccountQuoteList (used by Account Quote List)

Each component provides a specific functionality, such as displaying information about an account, quote, or policy.
title: Broker Digital Experience Site Components for Insurance
